    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@fperez do we have official preferences for how sphinxified docstrings should be?  I've typically avoided using `.. sourcecode:: ipython` in docstrings for interactive methods, because it is a detriment to their appearance in unrendered views (e.g. `method?`), and prevents a simple rest-renderer without Sphinx extensions from being able to draw them.\n"
  },
