    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@minrk, I hadn't really thought much about it so far, but we might as well now.  My gut tells me that we should draw the line at _not_ requring sphinx itself to render docstrings well.  Eventually I'm sure we'll end up having an optional docutils-based tool to parse docstrings for `?`, that can produce basic HTML as well as a cleaned-up plaintext.  I think having to rely on full-blown sphinx for that task is a bit over the top.\n\nSo perhaps a good guideline is: plain reST for docstrings, fancier sphinx extensions OK for the rest of the docs themselves.  How does that sound?\n"
  },
